(105, 1, '2018-07-03 12:05:45', '2018-07-03 09:05:45', '[rev_slider alias="slider1"]\r\n\r\nThe basis of the economy of the city are trade, transport and communications, construction. In regards to the contribution to GDP of trade sector of Kazakhstan''s economy Astana ranks second among the regions and cities of Republican significance after Almaty. The total regional product of two cities - Almaty and Astana-accounts for more than half of the total trade of Kazakhstan. The volume of retail turnover in Astana ranks second in the country.\r\n\r\nAstana is a leader in the Republic in terms of construction.\r\n\r\nThe city''s industrial production is concentrated mainly in the production of building materials, food/beverages, mechanical engineering. Astana holds the leading position in Kazakhstan in manufacture of structural metal products, concrete, ready for use, and construction of concrete products. Besides, the city has a relatively high proportion in the production of building metal constructions, radiators and Central heating boilers and lifting equipment.\r\n\r\nA special economic zone "Astana – new city" operates in the city to attract investors and develop new competitive industries.  Advantages of free economic zone (FEZ) is the presence of a special legal regime providing for tax and customs privileges. Projects of various fields are implemented in the territory of FEZ.  In particular, the development of the city focused on creating a competitive economy with a high share of innovative products in total production, developed sectors of the manufacturing industry (manufacture of building materials, food industry, etc.), small business providing a significant proportion of the gross regional product of the city and a developed tourism sector. Organized on 67 acres of the former "Tselinselmash" business incubator JSC "Astanatechnopark" provides the premises for over one hundred owners of companies and 150 tenants engaged in the manufacture of metal structures, equipment, consumer goods (utensils, clothing and household goods). Bakery and confectionery products, furniture and joinery products are produced and cars are repaired there. In this territory, there are five higher and five secondary schools, where about 5000 students get education.', 'Economy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'test-6-en', '', '', '2018-07-03 15:37:24', '2018-07-03 12:37:24', '', 0, 'http://localhost/desc/?p=105', 0, 'post', '', 0),
