(276, 1, '2018-07-03 23:51:16', '2018-07-03 20:51:16', '[rev_slider alias="slider1"]\r\n\r\n[rev_slider alias="slider2"]\r\n\r\n“Atameken” map of Kazakhstan” (motherland) ethno-memorial complex it was built at the initiative of the President of the Republic of Kazakhstan  Nursultan Nazarbaev on 8<sup>th</sup> September, 2001. Such ways of introducing history to its nation is widespread in most countries. In familiarizing with the geography of our adorable Motherland, teaching young generation to feel their holy country as a mother, “Atameken” map of Kazakhstan” ethno-memorial complex is almost like a textbook. But there is no need to hang this map on the wall or teacher’s stick. Because everything here is almost real. In the area of two football pitches or 1.7 hectares you can see Kyzylkum’s rice and cotton fields, Karagandy’s coal, Mangistau’s oil, old Burabay, Korgaljyn’s birds and Kaspi’s beautiful swans, Alatau’s snowy mountains, everything is in front of you. 14 regions and Almaty, Astana are illustrated on the map. Among different Natural-climate areas and landscapes, architectural exhibits historical and cultural monuments are placed notably. Guests from al over Kazakhstan feel really proud of their nation when they come here. More than 300 prototypes made by a master indicate his love to his country. Approximately 40 prototypes show the left side of the Esil River. Most of the exhibits in the memorial complex are designed and made by the team of the architects and designers of this very complex. What is interesting about the complex is that the time for accomplishing the map is not definite due to the reason that the city is prospering day by day and new building are built every day. For example, “Khan Shatyr” which put into operation for the 10 years anniversary of Astana, Independence Hall and other buildings can be found here as well. Upbringing and educating is considered to be one of the pivotal factors. Round-table and conferences are held here in the conference halls. E-map that illustrates flora and fauna, natural resources, main motor and railway routes of the Republic is really helpful in giving lectures for students. With the support of the Municipal Education Department, competition is held every year among high school students on history of their homeland. Winners can be honorably nominated as “the best guides” and are be able to work in the complex in the summer.', '“Atameken” map of Kazakhstan” (motherland) ethno-memorial complex (2001)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'atameken-map-of-kazakhstan-motherland-ethno-memorial-complex-2001', '', '', '2018-07-03 23:51:16', '2018-07-03 20:51:16', '', 0, 'http://localhost/desc/?p=276', 0, 'post', '', 0),
