(307, 1, '2018-07-04 00:21:48', '2018-07-03 21:21:48', '[rev_slider alias="slider1"]\r\n\r\n[rev_slider alias="slider2"]\r\n\r\n“Kazakh eli” is a cultural and architectural monument located in the capital of the Republic of Kazakhstan. It was built in 2009 and it is the masterpiece of Sarsenbek Zhunisov and Zhanbyrshy Nurkenov.\r\n\r\nDescription:\r\n\r\nThe whole area of the historical memorial complex is 5.2 hectare. And the central platform where the monument is located takes 1 hectare. The height of the monument made of white marble is 91 meters. This symbolizes the year (1991) Kazakhstan got its independence. The gigantic bird embellished with golden color on the top of the monument is Smuryk and it is “guarding” the piece in Kazakhstan. The color of the monument is white which discloses loyalty, kindness and honesty of the people of Kazakhstan. Such frames in other countries might be in black or red color, which is associated with power and blood.\r\n\r\nThere is a white dome column that is consisted of 28 similar columns and of 120 meters long. The frame is in the middle of the white column and located on the square shaped red granite platform. It is in the shape of square to show that Kazakhstan welcomes everyone from all over the world with its generosity and hospitality.\r\n\r\nChanges: platform is to be built into the four edges of the granite. The height will be 20.1 meters, and copper reliefs are being erected by the decision of the artistic council. According to the creators, this can reflect the true meaning and brilliance of the monument.\r\n\r\nCentral bas-relief is called “The people and the President”. We can see the first president of the Republic of Kazakhstan and the people there. The first piece is 5 meters high and it illustrates the moment when Nazarbaev was signing the Constitution and swearing. This embodies that the law rules the county. The people are Kazakhstani people, and swallows flying expresses piece and unity.', 'Monument “Kazakh eli” (Kazakh homeland) (2009)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'monument-kazakh-eli-kazakh-homeland-2009', '', '', '2018-07-04 00:21:48', '2018-07-03 21:21:48', '', 0, 'http://localhost/desc/?p=307', 0, 'post', '', 0),
