(380, 1, '2018-07-04 01:31:21', '2018-07-03 22:31:21', '[rev_slider alias="slider1"]\r\n\r\n[rev_slider alias="slider2"]\r\n\r\nThe Nur-Astana mosque opened on March 22, 2005 is projected by Lebanese master Charles Hafizah and built by Turkish company "Pasiner" with the financial support of the state of Qatar. Nur-Astana is the second largest mosque in Central Asia after the mosque Hazrat Sultan.\r\n\r\nThe size of the mosque is truly amazing: the mosque has four minarets with a height of 62 meters, the height of the main dome is 43 meters and a total area of 3930 m2. The structure is made of glass, concrete, granite and Alucobond . For up to 5 000 people  can pray in the building of the mosque at the same time.\r\n\r\nThese numbers are not random: Allah has appeared to Mohammed when he was 40 years old, and in his earthly life lasted 63 years. Eight spores, which are engraved excerpts of texts from the Koran – Suras – supporting the main dome of the mosque. A wide courtyard with a large fountain lies in front of the mosque.\r\n\r\nThe main room of the mosque is a large hall with seats for about 5,000 people came to pray.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'The Central mosque "Nur – Astana" (2005)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-central-mosque-nur-astana-2005', '', '', '2018-07-04 01:31:21', '2018-07-03 22:31:21', '', 0, 'http://localhost/desc/?p=380', 0, 'post', '', 0),
