(386, 1, '2018-07-04 01:37:53', '2018-07-03 22:37:53', '[rev_slider alias="slider1"]\r\n\r\n[rev_slider alias="slider2"]\r\n\r\nThe heart of the Palace is the ice arena, which consists of ice track of 400 meters with stands for 8,000 seats, two hockey courts, a hall of Judicial Board, hall for press conferences, 15 dressing rooms for the athletes.\r\n\r\nThe Palace is designed for training and competitions in speed skating, short track speed skating, ice hockey, figure skating.\r\n\r\nBy combining perfection of the technical equipment and the uniqueness of the architectural project, the staff of IP "Alau" set a goal to enter the ranks of the best flatland rinks of the world. 9 continental records have been established during the 7 th Asian winter Games at the Ice Palace. "Alau" not only gained the status of Kazakhstan forge records, but also took 6th place (from 641 possible) in the world ranking speed skating stadiums.\r\n\r\nThe Ice Palace holds major international competitions and training camps. Pupils of sports school # 2 and private sports clubs Palace-skating, short track, figure skating, ice hockey and ball train on the ice in "Alau". Champion ice is available for recreational athletes - in the days of public skating each person can stand on skates. This is the concept of mass accessibility, the task of which is to popularize winter sports and contribute to the development of mass sport in Astana.', 'Ice Palace Alau (2011)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ice-palace-alau-2011', '', '', '2018-07-04 01:37:53', '2018-07-03 22:37:53', '', 0, 'http://localhost/desc/?p=386', 0, 'post', '', 0),
