(392, 1, '2018-07-04 01:43:31', '2018-07-03 22:43:31', '[rev_slider alias="slider1"]\r\n\r\n[rev_slider alias="slider2"]\r\n\r\nUniversal concert hall for                3500 seats – a unique building not only by capacity, but also by the acoustic possibilities. The concert hall is located on the Main square, successfully blending in with the building of the presidential Residence "AK Orda", buildings of the Senate and the Majilis of the Supreme court.\r\n\r\nCDC "Kazakhstan" owes to the Italian architect Manfredi Nicoletti, one of Europe''s leading architects for its unusual external appearance.\r\n\r\nInside and outside the concert hall is covered by special wood, which allows to fully express its high acoustic properties. The walls have various mechanisms to optimize the sound. Impressive acoustic effect is largely due to the unusual shape of the atrium, which is made in the form of national musical instrument – dombra.\r\n\r\nIn addition, there are fastening curtains on the walls with ability to repel and attract sound. Spectator seats also have acoustic panels boast.\r\n\r\nThe decoration of the facade, which used innovative materials that protect the building from temperature extremes, characteristic for the area and salt winds - is also attractive. There are no such original structure in any country.', 'Concert Hall "Kazakhstan" (2009)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'concert-hall-kazakhstan-2009', '', '', '2018-07-04 01:43:31', '2018-07-03 22:43:31', '', 0, 'http://localhost/desc/?p=392', 0, 'post', '', 0),
