(430, 1, '2018-07-04 02:31:56', '2018-07-03 23:31:56', '[rev_slider alias="slider1"]\r\n\r\n[rev_slider alias="slider2"]\r\n\r\nHosting EXPO-2017 International Specialized Exhibition in Astana is one of the key projects of Kazakhstan. The initiative to host a large scale event in the capital of the country belongs to President Nursultan Nazarbayev.\r\n\r\nOn June 10, 2011 Kazakhstan’s bid was officially presented in Paris to the Secretary General of the International Exhibitions Bureau (IEB) Vincent Gonzales Loscertales. From that moment on, Kazakhstan officially joined the competition to host EXPO-2017 in Astana.\r\n\r\nOn June 12, 2012 official presentation of Astana’s bid to host EXPO-2017 was held at the 151st General Assembly of the IEB in Paris, which included a video address of the President of Kazakhstan. In his speech, Nursultan Nazarbayev said the country would make every effort for the successful organisation of exhibition in its capital city.\r\n\r\nThe theme of the exhibition is the “Energy of the Future” and is dedicated to the alternative energy sources and “green” technologies.\r\n\r\nOn November 22, 2012 as a result of secret ballot voting, which involved 161 member states of the International Exhibitions Bureau, Astana was chosen as the venue to host EXPO-2017, receiving 103 votes.\r\n\r\nOn November 26, 2012 President Nursultan Nazarbayev signed the Decree №436 “On the establishment of the State Commission for the preparation and holding of the International Specialized Exhibition EXPO-2017”.\r\n\r\nIn April 2014, the President launched the construction of EXPO-2017 exhibition complex located near the Nazarbayev University.\r\n\r\nThe total area of the exhibition stands at 174 hectares.\r\n\r\nKazakhstan is a member of the International Exhibitions Bureau since 1997 and has been taking part in EXPO since 2005.', 'ASTANA EXPO 2017', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'astana-expo-2017', '', '', '2018-07-04 02:31:56', '2018-07-03 23:31:56', '', 0, 'http://localhost/desc/?p=430', 0, 'post', '', 0),
